newsitem.title: USA: FCOJ futures end weaker, seen heading lower.
newsitem.headline: FCOJ futures end weaker, seen heading lower.

text.p: NYCE Frozen concentrated orange juice futures settled a dull session slightly lower as a dearth of news ahead of the weekend kept most players out of the ring, floor sources said.
Volume on the day was estimated at only 500 lots.
November FCOJ closed 0.40 cent lower at 106.45 cents a lb after trading from 106.70 to 106.00. The rear closed 0.45 lower to 3.00 higher.
On the charts, prices appear to be heading lower, analysts said, pegging nearby support between 105.00 and 104.00, and then between 98.00 and 96.00.
USDA will release its widely-watched estimate for the Florida crop next month.
